eep non-service value/object-mapping tests as fallback coverage, because the reported java-run failure is in object mapping and may be fixable without a database.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Docker startup can make tests slower and more failure-prone than pure value/object-mapping coverage.\",\n    \"Using Testcontainers inside native-image tests may introduce unrelated reachability needs; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\",\n    \"The current failure appears to be an assertion/behavior change in object mapping, so database setup may not be necessary for the minimal fix.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_054bf7602eea0994016a42715dbd4c8190a5de26062e0e2f60\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3626, "output": 1269, "cacheRead": 65024, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 69919, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782739279897, "responseId": "resp_054bf7602eea0994016a4271513f608190ab7bcdbfb33fa891"}, "toolResults": []}
